Q. Given a binary array nums, return the maximum number of consecutive 1's in the array.

Explanation: First initialize 2 points- left and right o 0;
             start the window, 
          if the element in the array is 1, update max count using the logic Math.max(max, right-left+1);
          else left is incremented to a place after right -> becuase you are breaking a streak and moving forward to the point after current right. 



class Solution {
    public int findMaxConsecutiveOnes(int[] nums) {
        int max=0;
        int left=0; int right =0;
        int n=nums.length;
        while(right<n){
            if(nums[right]==1){
                max=Math.max(max, right-left+1);
            }
            else{
                left=right+1;
            }
            right++;
        }
        return max;
    }
}
